This class is a model within the MVC architecture. It holds the methods used for a user's interaction with the web service. Elastic Search is used to search through the web service. Gson is used to handle recipe objects

searchRecipes

public java.util.ArrayList<Recipe> searchRecipes(java.lang.String str,
                                                 boolean ingredient)
                                          throws org.apache.http.client.ClientProtocolException,
                                                 java.io.IOException
Searches for recipes on the web service by keywords or ingredients. The query string is based on whether or not an ingredient search is used. This variable will differ if searching by keyword instead. Keywords are based on a Recipe's "tag" array. The tag array includes a recipe's category, author name, and title. By using this tag array, we were able to implement a universal search for a recipe.

Parameters:
str - the ingredients or keyword to be queried
ingredient - if we are searching by ingredients then true. False if search by keyword
Returns:
an ArrayList of found recipes
Throws:
org.apache.http.client.ClientProtocolException
java.io.IOException
See Also:
search by ingredients using "See What I Can Make" button, search by keyword using the edit box in activity
